c("Begin at least 4 hours in advance or, preferably, the night before. Trim fat  from flank steak and cut into strips approximately 1/2 inch wide and 3 inches  long.", "In hot oil, brown the steak strips over medium high heat until they are  cooked through and brown.", "Don't overcook or steak will be tough.", "Drain off any  excess fat. Put steak strips in a 1-quart bowl and pour over the well-blended  Italian dressing.", "Refrigerate for at least 3-1/2 hours or overnight. Open  artichokes and drain off all liquid.", 
