c("Use a 14 to 20 qt. pan.", "Coarsely chop enough onions and carrots to make 1 cup each.", "In pan, place onions and carrots, corned beef with any liquid from meat, vinegar, stout, mustard seed, coriander, peppercorns, dill, allspice, and bay leaves.", "Add water to barely cover beef.", "Cover pan and bring to a boil over high heat.", "Simmer till meat is tender when pierced, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.", "Meanwhile, cut remaining onions into wedges.", "Cut remaining carrots into 2 inch lengths, halve them lengthwise if large.", 
